President Barack Obama will be holding a news conference on Wednesday, April 29th at 8:00 PM EDT at the White House. Members of the media who wish to attend must apply for credentials by Monday, April 27th. Even current White House hard pass holders must apply. The deadline to apply is 12:00 PM EDT on Monday. Media members who do not currently hold a White House hard pass must also email their full name, date of birth, social security number, and country of citizenship to press@who.eop.gov. Riser positions have already been allocated, but a pool feed will be available. Applicants will be notified by 6:00 PM EDT on Tuesday, April 28th if their credentials have been granted, and they will receive logistical information.